President Biden welcomed President Herzog of Israel back to the White House. They discussed the deep-rooted friendship between the United States and Israel and the progress made in bringing stability and integration in the Middle East. President Biden affirmed America's commitment to Israel and ensuring that Iran never acquires a nuclear weapon. President Herzog expressed gratitude for the strong cooperation between the two countries and discussed the internal situation in Israel, emphasizing the strength of Israeli democracy. The press also asked about a possible invitation for Prime Minister Netanyahu to visit the White House, to which President Biden responded that they are in talks.